---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../config/site";
---

<MainLayout title="Privacy Policy">
  <article class="panel policy">
    <h1>Crystord: Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: December 10, 2025</p>

    <section>
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>Crystord is a software platform that enables synchronisation and management of data between
      various sources. The Crystord Google Workspace Add-on provides features similar to the core
      Crystord platform, allowing users to seamlessly integrate and update content between Google
      Sheets™ and Google Slides™. This privacy policy explains how your information is handled when
      you use the Crystord platform and its Google Add-on.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Collection and Access</h2>
      <p>When you use the Crystord platform or install the Crystord Google Add-on, the application
      accesses the following specific Google user data:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google Sheets™ Content:</strong> Read access to the specific spreadsheets you
        select to synchronise data.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Slides™ Content:</strong> Read and write access to the specific
        presentations you are editing to update charts or text.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>These permissions are required solely to enable the synchronisation and management features
      provided by Crystord.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Usage</h2>
      <p>Crystord's use of your Google User Data accessed from Google APIs adheres to Google's
      Limited Use Requirements. Specifically, we use your data to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Synchronise Content:</strong> Transfer data values from your Sheets to your
        Slides presentations upon your request.</li>
        <li><strong>Display Information:</strong> Show your spreadsheet data within the Add-on
        sidebar to help you select what to sync.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Crystord does not use your data for advertising, profiling, or any unauthorised purposes.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>We do not share your Google User Data with any third parties. Specifically:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No Third-Party Sharing:</strong> Your data is not sold, traded, or transferred
        to outside parties.</li>
        <li><strong>No AI Training:</strong> Your data is not used to train artificial intelligence
        models.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Data is only transferred to Google's servers as necessary to execute the Add-on's functions
      (e.g., calling the Slides API).</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Storage and Protection</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No External Storage:</strong> Crystord does not store your Google Sheets™ or
        Slides™ data on external servers. All data resides within your own Google Drive.</li>
        <li><strong>Security Measures:</strong> All communication between the Add-on and Google
        services occurs over HTTPS. Since the application runs within Google Apps Script, it
        benefits from Google's native security infrastructure.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Exception Logging</h2>
      <p>Crystord uses Google's Cloud Logging for exception logging. This logging is limited to
      technical error messages and does not include user content or personal data. Exception logs
      are used solely for debugging and reliability improvements.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>User Controls</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You can revoke the Add-on's access to your Google account at any time through your
        Google Account security settings at
        <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">myaccount.google.com/permissions</a>.</li>
        <li>You may uninstall the Add-on or discontinue use of the Crystord platform whenever
        you wish.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
      <h3>Data Retention</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google User Data:</strong> Crystord does not retain your Google Sheets™ or
        Google Slides™ content on external servers. All data operations occur within Google's
        infrastructure and your Google account.</li>
        <li><strong>Configuration Data:</strong> Any configuration settings (such as Sheet™ IDs
        or names) are stored within your Slides™ data properties and are not transmitted to
        external servers.</li>
        <li><strong>Exception Logs:</strong> Technical error logs are retained for up to 30 days
        for debugging purposes, then automatically deleted.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Data Deletion</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Automatic Deletion:</strong> Since Crystord operates entirely within Google's
        environment, no user data is stored externally that requires deletion.</li>
        <li><strong>Access Revocation:</strong> When you revoke the Add-on's permissions through
        your Google Account settings, all access to your data is immediately terminated.</li>
        <li><strong>Add-on Removal:</strong> Uninstalling the Add-on removes all associated
        permissions and stops any data access.</li>
        <li><strong>User Rights:</strong> You have the right to request confirmation that no
        personal data is being stored externally by contacting us at
        <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>{siteConfig.contactEmail}</a>.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Compliance</h2>
      <p>Crystord's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs will adhere to the
      Google API Services User Data Policy, including the Limited Use Requirements. This means your
      data is used only as necessary to provide or improve user-facing features and is never sold or
      used for unauthorised purposes.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>This privacy policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this
      page with an updated revision date.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this privacy policy or the Crystord platform,
      please contact us at
      <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>{siteConfig.contactEmail}</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <p class="trademark">
      <small>Google Sheets™ and Google Slides™ are trademarks of Google LLC.</small>
    </p>
  </article>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .policy section {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .policy h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .policy h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--brand-ink);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .policy ul {
    padding-left: 1.4rem;
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0.8rem;
  }

  .policy li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .meta {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: -0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .trademark {
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
</style>
